eq= 29 CFI=0.45 | # extract\r\n\r\n=== STRONG CAUSAL ANCHORS (high frequency + high CFI) ===\r\n  freq= 60 CFI=1.00 | llm response <think>\r\n  freq= 60 CFI=1.00 | ## applied\r\n  freq= 60 CFI=1.00 | next instantiation\r\n  freq= 60 CFI=1.00 | ## llm\r\n  freq= 60 CFI=1.00 | tic\r\n  freq= 60 CFI=1.00 | ## applied mutations\r\n  freq= 60 CFI=1.00 | pulse\r\n  freq= 60 CFI=1.00 | variant\r\n  freq= 60 CFI=1.00 | - completed\r\n  freq= 60 CFI=1.00 | invariant\r\n\r\nFull results written to: C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\CFI_RESULTS.md","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774361131342}}
{"type":"message","id":"a5106c06","parentId":"6ead164c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:05:50.703Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The analysis ran and the results are very interesting. Let me now analyze the findings and write a research document.\n\nKey findings:\n1. 142/2491 (5.7%) of invariants have high CFI (>=0.7) — true causal anchors\n2. 1116/2491 (44.8%) of invariants have ZERO CFI — purely noise\n3. Mean CFI is only 0.181 — most frequency-based \"invariants\" don't predict anything\n4. The top invariants are structural patterns like \"llm response\", \"pulse\", \"invariant\", \"variant\" — these are structural markers\n\n\n5. There's a critical mismatch: the highest-frequency invariants like \"next action is\" have only ~0.47 CFI, showing that frequency is a poor proxy for actual causal relationships. The real causal anchors are lower-frequency but structurally fundamental patterns like \"tic\" and \"invariant/variant classification\".\n\nThe core insight is that frequency conflates two distinct categories — high-frequency structural noise like code markers and function names versus genuinely causal patterns that appear less often but carry predictive power. I need to filter by CFI rather than frequency to extract the true causal structure, then test whether a CFI-thresholded approach outperforms the frequency baseline.","thinkingSignature":"bc254dc162313d102fb8d538f641e341ddfcfdf0be8b6427399c379dbf127bb4"},{"type":"text","text":"Results are striking. Now let me commit this and write the research document:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sd0z7emhtp0h_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd \"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/sandbox\" && git add scripts/cfi_analysis.py && git commit -m \"CFI analysis: frequency invariants are mostly noise (1116/2491 have CFI=0)\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29754,"output":350,"cacheRead":12050,"cacheWrite":