{"type":"message","id":"909e39b0","parentId":"31b55f91","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:07:40.189Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me update the current_goals.md to reflect what was accomplished.","thinkingSignature":"7d11886f431cd03d97c78b4eda6223b8dfb5649a18fd47b7fb949550e71e0d73"},{"type":"text","text":"Now update current_goals:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dpm4ebl6eryw_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/sandbox/state/current_goals.md","old_string":"## Pending\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\n- [ ] Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY (2026-03-23)\n- **Insight:** Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\n- **New doc:** `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\n- **Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure — compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\n- **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) — test on last 20 pulse logs\n- **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n- **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\n\n### NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)","new_string":"## Phase 1 Advancement: CFI Analysis ✅ (2026-03-24)\n- **New doc:** `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\n- **Finding:** 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise)\n- **Finding:** Only 5.7% of invariants have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\n- **Finding:** Mean CFI is 0.181 — frequency-based compression is mostly signal loss\n- **Key insight:** Two types of persistence — Process (CFI=0, metaprogramming artifacts) vs Research Trajectory (CFI>0.7, causal)\n- **Next:** CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare vs frequency baseline)\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\n- [ ] Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34885,"output":608,"cacheRead":12050,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47543,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774361246090}}
