\n-36 - **Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure — compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\n-37 - **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) — test on last 20 pulse logs\n-38 - **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n-39 - **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\n-40 \n-41 ### NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\n-42 - [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\n-43 - [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\n-44 - [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\n-45 - [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\n-46 \n 47 ## Key Insights from This Session\n 48 \n 49 1. **The gap IS the compression** — session boundaries are temporal hashing\n 50 2. **λ encodes both** — decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n    ...","firstChangedLine":26},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774361260195}}
